Q : Given a string s consisting of words and spaces, return the length of the last word in the string.
A word is a maximal substring consisting of non-space characters only.


Sol :


class Solution {
public:
    int lengthOfLastWord(string s) {
        int n = s.length();
        int cnt = 0;
        int i = n-1;
        while(i>=0 && s[i]==' ') {
            i--;
        }
        while(i>=0 && s[i]!=' ') {
            cnt++;
            i--;
        }
        return cnt;
    }
};

 
